name: Bug report
description: Report a reproducible defect in {{PROJECT_NAME}}
labels: ["fix"]
assignees: ["{{OWNER}}"]
body:
  - type: markdown
    attributes:
      value: |
        Thanks for the report. A maintainer **reproduces and root-causes** before a
        `docs/bugs/` record is opened, so a minimal reproduction is the most useful thing you
        can provide. **Security issues do not go here** — see [`SECURITY.md`](../../SECURITY.md).
  - type: input
    id: version
    attributes:
      label: Affected version
      placeholder: "vX.Y.Z (or commit SHA)"
    validations:
      required: true
  - type: input
    id: env
    attributes:
      label: Platform / toolchain
      placeholder: "OS, {{LANG_NAME}} version, build tool"
    validations:
      required: true
  - type: textarea
    id: repro
    attributes:
      label: Minimal reproduction
      description: Steps to reproduce, or (ideally) a failing test.
    validations:
      required: true
  - type: textarea
    id: behavior
    attributes:
      label: Expected vs actual behavior
    validations:
      required: true
